<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900920-0017</DOCNO><DOCID>900920-0017.</DOCID><HL>   CBOT and CME to Study   Unifying Some Functions</HL><DATE>09/20/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C14</SO><IN>SECURITIES (SCR)COMMODITY NEWS, FARM PRODUCTS (CMD)</IN><LP>   CHICAGO -- The Chicago Board of Trade and the ChicagoMercantile Exchange said they have formed a joint committeeto explore ways to cut costs and increase efficiency byunifying certain functions, procedures and operations.   The committee will focus specifically on the areas ofinternational marketing, systems development, operations andclearing, the CBOT and CME said.</LP><TEXT>   The joint effort is part of &quot;a new era of cooperation,&quot;said one committee member. The CME and CBOT agreed inprinciple this year to become partners in Globex, anautomated after-hours trading system being developed inconjunction with Reuters Holdings PLC. The two are alsosharing the costs of developing AUDIT, a hand-held computerterminal for recording trades.</TEXT></DOC>